        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 4:56PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles south of Braddock, or 14 miles northeast of Linton. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northeastern Emmons
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring.</instruction>
